  <p>
    The slight shift of <strong>{{ metrics.gini_shift | default(-0.0124) | round(4) }}</strong> points in Gini is a standard industry finding. This adjustment corrects for selection bias and ensures the scorecard remains stable and predictive across the full spectrum of future credit applicants.
  </p>

